        <p class="text-small">
          Irrigation is the artificial process of applying controlled amounts of water to land to assist in production
          of crops. Irrigation helps to grow agricultural crops, maintain landscapes, and revegetate disturbed soils
          in dry areas and during periods of less than average rainfall. Irrigation also has other uses in crop
          production, including frost protection, suppressing weed growth in grain fields and preventing soil
          consolidation. In contrast, agriculture that relies only on direct rainfall is referred to as rain-fed.
        </p>

